     8â†’# Structs
    10â†’Structs contains various utilities to work with Go (Golang) structs. It was
    11â†’initially used by me to convert a struct into a `map[string]interface{}`. With
    12â†’time I've added other utilities for structs.  It's basically a high level
    13â†’package based on primitives from the reflect package. Feel free to add new
    14â†’functions or improve the existing code.
    15â†’
    16â†’## Install
    18â†’```bash
    19â†’go get github.com/fatih/structs
    20â†’```
    21â†’
    22â†’## Usage and Examples
    24â†’Just like the standard lib `strings`, `bytes` and co packages, `structs` has
    25â†’many global functions to manipulate or organize your struct data. Lets define
    26â†’and declare a struct:
    27â†’
    28â†’```go
    29â†’type Server struct {
    30â†’	Name        string `json:"name,omitempty"`
    31â†’	ID          int
    32â†’	Enabled     bool
    33â†’	users       []string // not exported
    34â†’	http.Server          // embedded
    35â†’}
    36â†’
    37â†’server := &Server{
    38â†’	Name:    "gopher",
    39â†’	ID:      123456,
    40â†’	Enabled: true,
    41â†’}
    42â†’```
    43â†’
    44â†’```go
